\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b neglecta} ({\i C. neglecta} subsp.{\i  stricta} (Scop.) Vierh.): Plant 10-50 cm. Stems solitary and erect or several and decumbent, more or less hispidulous below, glabrescent above. Basal leaves up to 14 × 3 cm, denticulate to pinnatisect. Involucre glabrous, tomentulose or glandular-pubescent, rarely with greenish, eglandular hairs near the apex of the inner bracts. Achenes gradually attenuate to the apex but not beaked, the marginal not enfolded in or retained by the inner bracts. 2n = 8.{\i  Throughout the range of the species}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b corymbosa} (Ten.) Nyman,{\i  Consp.} 460 (1879): Plant up to 40 cm. Stems branched from the base, with slender, yellow rigid hairs. Basal leaves up to 17 × 2 cm, denticulate to pinnatisect. Involucre usually with numerous yellow or greenish eglandular hairs, sometimes glabrous or nearly so. Achenes with a beak less than 1 mm, the marginal enfolded in and often retained by the inner bracts. 2n = 8. •{\i  Italy, Sicilia, Greece}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b fuliginosa} (Sibth. & Sm.) Vierh., {\i Verh. Zool.-Bot. Ges. Wien}{\b  69}: 269 (1919) ({\i C. fuliginosa} Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  C. neglecta }var.{\i  graeca} (Vierh.) Hayek): Plant dwarf, with several sparingly branched stems. Basal leaves 2-6(-8) × 1-2 cm, denticulate to pinnatisect with 4-6 pairs of lateral segments. Involucre glabrescent or tomentulose, with short glandular and eglandular hairs or with very slender, green, eglandular hairs. Achenes with a stout beak. 2n = 6.{\i  Greece and Aegean region}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b cretica} (Boiss.) Vierh.,{\i  op. cit.} 268 (1919): Plant dwarf, with numerous, sparingly branched stems. Basal leaves up to 7 × 0·5-1·5 cm, dentate to pinnatisect with 6-10 pairs of lateral segments. Involucre glabrous, tomentulose, or minutely glandular-hairy, sometimes with longer eglandular hairs. Achenes with a short, slender beak. 2n = 8. •{\i  Kriti and Karpathos}.
