\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 63. C. suffreniana} (DC.) Lloyd,{\i  Fl. Loire-Inf. }155 (1844). Annual; stems 3-35 cm, usually many, branched from the base. Leaves with eglandular hairs, or glabrous; basal 0·7-9 × 0·3-1·8 cm, spathulate to oblanceolate, obtuse to acute, denticulate to runcinate-pinnatifid, narrowed at base; cauline lanceolate, acute to acuminate, sessile, semiamplexicaul, auriculate. Involucre with 10-12 linear outer bracts ¼-½ as long as the 10-16 linear-lanceolate inner ones. Achenes 3-4 × 0·3-0·4 mm, narrowed to a slender beak, 10-ribbed. •{\i  S. & W. France, S. & W. Italy.} Ga It.
